solution:
The expression $24x^2-19x-35$ can be factored as $(3x-5)(8x+7)$. Therefore, $(Ax-5)=(3x-5)$ and $(2Bx+C)=(8x+7)$. From that, $A=3$, $B=4$, and $C=7$. \begin{align*}
AB-3C&=3\cdot4-3\cdot7\\
&=12-21\\
&=\boxed{-9}
\end{align*}

Multiply both numerator and denominator by $\sqrt3$: \begin{align*}
\sqrt{\frac23} &= \frac{\sqrt2}{\sqrt3}\\
&=\frac{\sqrt2}{\sqrt3}\cdot\frac{\sqrt3}{\sqrt3}\\
